# Testing Standards

## What to Test

| Layer | What to test |
|-------|-------------|
| Services | Correct fetch call, error throwing on non-success response, response parsing |
| Feature hooks | Correct query key used, service called with the right token and args |
| Form hooks | Field update, validation, reset, `loadForEdit` pre-fill |
| Components | Renders correctly, user interactions, loading/empty state display |

## File Co-location

Place test files next to the file under test:

```
useFeatureData.ts
useFeatureData.test.ts
feature.ts          ← service
feature.test.ts
FeatureCard.tsx
FeatureCard.test.tsx
```

## Mocking Services

Mock the service module — not `fetch` directly:

```typescript
import { featureService } from '@/services/feature';
vi.mock('@/services/feature');

const mockGetAll = vi.mocked(featureService.getAll).mockResolvedValue([mockFeature]);
```

## Mocking Auth

```typescript
vi.mock('@/contexts/AuthContext', () => ({
  useAuth: () => ({
    user: { uid: 'user-1', getIdToken: () => Promise.resolve('mock-token') },
  }),
}));
```

## React Query Test Wrapper

Always wrap hook tests in a `QueryClientProvider` with `retry: false`:

```typescript
const wrapper = ({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) => (
  <QueryClientProvider
    client={new QueryClient({ defaultOptions: { queries: { retry: false } } })}
  >
    {children}
  </QueryClientProvider>
);

const { result } = renderHook(() => useFeatureData(), { wrapper });
await waitFor(() => expect(result.current.isSuccess).toBe(true));
expect(mockGetAll).toHaveBeenCalledWith('mock-token');
```

## Mutation Testing

```typescript
const { result } = renderHook(() => useFeatureMutations(), { wrapper });
act(() => result.current.createFeature({ title: 'Test', description: '' }));
await waitFor(() => expect(result.current.isSubmitting).toBe(false));
expect(mockCreate).toHaveBeenCalledWith('mock-token', { title: 'Test', description: '' });
```
